A Dockerfile is a text file that contains instructions to build a Docker image step-by-step.
It always follows a top â†’ bottom execution order.
Basic Dockerfile Structure
 # 1. Base Image
    FROM image_name:tag

# 2. Maintainer info (optional)
    LABEL maintainer="yourname"

# 3. Set Working Directory
    WORKDIR /app

# 4. Copy files
    COPY . .

# 5. Install dependencies
    RUN command

# 6. Expose port
    EXPOSE port_number

# 7. Default command to run
    CMD ["executable", "arg"]
